is_empty()

Description
    bool is_empty(mixed $v)
    Performs a number of tests upon the parameter, $v, to determine whether it is empty.
	
Parameters
    v
		A variable, $var, of any type may be passed to the function.
		
Return Values
    Returns a boolean value.  The value is TRUE if the variable meets the EngineCMS definitions for an empty variable in the Notes section.  The value is otherwise FALSE.
	
Examples
	<?php
		...
		if (isset($attPairs['select']) && !is_empty($attPairs['select'])) {
			$whereClause .= "WHERE ";
			$selectArray  = explode(",",$attPairs['select']);
			foreach ($selectArray as $item) {
				$whereClause .= (($whereClause != "WHERE ")?" OR ":"").$attPairs['valuecol']."='".$item."'";
			}
		...
	?>

Notes
	EngineCMS defines an empty variable as one that:
	1. Returns FALSE when passed to isset();
	2. returns TRUE when passed to the EngineCMS function, isnull();
	3. is identical to the boolean value FALSE;
	4. is an array which is empty;
	5. after being trim()'ed, contains the string value "0" OR is of integer type and is equal to 0;
	6. or, after being trim()'ed, passes any of the previous criteria.
	In all of the above cases, is_empty returns boolean value TRUE, indicating that the variable is empty.
   
	Also view http://us3.php.net/manual/en/function.empty.php for a description of PHP's empty() function.
	
See Also
	isnull()